{
  "texts": [
    "The production workflow has four primary stages: filling, capping, labeling, and packaging.",
    "Each stage contains several other subcomponents, such as conveyor motors and production areas (information and data in Table 3), which are helpful in troubleshooting whenever faults occur.",
    "The small factory aims to align with I5.0 principles by focusing on workers' well-being.",
    "Unlike in I4.0 environments where achieving higher production was the primary goal, the factory focuses on its workers' well-being by monitoring maximum overtime hours to prevent overworking, preserving the ecosystem, continuously monitoring the factory pollution level, and ensuring that the production remains within the acceptable thresholds; by integrating technology to assist workers making swift decisions.",
    "Our GPT industrial chatbot plays this role effectively by helping operators closely monitor production while troubleshooting the system in case of faults utilizing a user-friendly natural language interface."
  ]
}